Just a day before President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the nation, various sectors of society have come together to hold what they call the ‘people’s State of the Nation Address. CAPE TOWN- Just a day before President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the nation, various sectors of society have come together to hold what they call the ‘people’s State of the Nation Address.
Main speakers include former public protector, Thuli Madonsela, Anti-apartheid stalwart Reverend Frank Chikane, Archbishop Thabo Makgoba as well as the SACP’s Solly Mapaila.
The event is taking place at the St. George’s Cathedral.